<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 29 at 10:03PM EST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Period of Slippery Roads Through Early Overnight...
Snow has spread over the area late this evening, including a
band of heavier snow from Rockford into the far northern suburbs.
The heaviest snow is expected to remain along and north of I-88,
but all locations can expect to see snow. A wintry mix has also
moved into areas south of the Kankakee River Valley and should
continue into early overnight as well.
Snow accumulations will occur on many paved surfaces, especially
on rural or less traveled roads. If traveling, be prepared for
sudden visibility reductions down to a half mile. The snow will
gradually diminish after midnight, with most locations receiving
less than one half inch, though isolated localized totals over one
inch are possible.</description>
